HEADWORD: Eking
<hw>Ek"ing</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From <er>Eke</er>,
<pos>v. t.</pos>]</ety> <fld>(Shipbuilding)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>A
lengthening or filling piece to make good a deficiency in length.</def>
<sd>(b)</sd> <def>The carved work under the quarter piece at the aft
part of the quarter gallery.</def> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>eiking</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>E-la</ent>⟦br⟧
